<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/571: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cox</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-31T17:00:00-04:00">August 31, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>115. For Braden. Your despatch 240, August 21. Major Weeks authorized to
                            act as observer. Submit estimate in accordance with the Department’s
                            instruction 417, July 17, 1936,<note n="44" xml:id="d61fn44">Not
                                printed.</note> and inform Department if necessary drafts will be
                            drawn at Santiago or Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>